snippet.title: AP names Klug to top SKorea editorial position
snippet.description: The Associated Press has named Seoul news editor Foster Klug as its chief of bureau for South Korea.

snippet.title: Rapids, Earthquakes play to scoreless tie
snippet.description: Alan Gordon hit the crossbar in the opening minute for San Jose and that was as close as the Earthquakes and the Colorado Rapids got to scoring in their 0-0 draw Saturday.

snippet.title: Strong earthquake strikes off Papua New Guinea
snippet.description: A powerful earthquake struck off the South Pacific nation of Papua New Guinea on Saturday, but there were no immediate reports of injuries or damage.

snippet.title: AP PHOTOS: Editor selections from Latin America
snippet.description: Holy Week is always a busy time for Associated Press photographers around Latin America. With sumptuous images from Mexico to Argentina, our photo staff once again recorded the religious season, with all its local idiosyncrasies.

snippet.title: Magnitude-7.2 earthquake shakes Mexican capital
snippet.description: A powerful magnitude-7.2 earthquake shook central and southern Mexico on Friday, sending panicked people into the streets. Some walls cracked and fell, but there were no reports of major damage or casualties.

snippet.title: Magnitude-7.2 earthquake strikes central, southern Mexico
snippet.description: The quake sends panicked people into the streets, but there are no reports of major damage or deaths.

snippet.title: American Top 30: Projecting Klinsmann's 2014 World Cup roster, 17th edition
snippet.description: Terrence Boyd rejoined the U.S. national team rankings with 2 goals for Rapid Vienna, while Alejandro Bedoya scored for Nantes.

snippet.title: MLS Capsules
snippet.description: New England Revolution goalkeeper Bobby Shuttleworth stopped Juan Luis Anangono's penalty kick in the first minute of stoppage time Saturday to preserve a 1-1 draw with the Chicago Fire, who matched a Major League Soccer record with their sixth straight tie.

snippet.title: Today in History
snippet.description: Today is Easter Sunday, April 20, the 110th day of 2014. There are 255 days left in the year.
